# Replit parallel environment

This repo is also developed and deployed on **Replit**. Replit owns its environment and configuration.

## Do not edit (Replit-owned)

- `.replit`
- `.replitignore`
- `replit.md`
- `.cache/` and `.local/` (Replit runtime; already gitignored)

Do not change Replit deployment settings, ports, workflows, `[agent]`, `[postMerge]`, `[nix]`, or module versions in `.replit`.

## Application code with Replit hooks

Vite configs and packages may reference `@replit/*` plugins for the Replit runtime. Avoid changing Replit-specific plugin blocks (e.g. `REPL_ID` guards, `@replit/vite-plugin-*`) unless the user explicitly asks and understands Replit impact.

## Cursor / GitHub workflow

- Develop on `cursor/live` (or feature branches) from Cursor.
- Let Replit manage its own config on its side; do not “fix” or sync Replit files from Cursor.
